#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1235
msgid ""
"The signed message in the upper part of the file lists several files along "
"with their respective SHA256 hashes. The listed files are installation "
"packages for all OSs and architectures for which Bitcoin Core is released. "
"The lower part of the file is the signature of the message in the upper "
"part. The signature commits to the entire message and thus to all the hashes"
" and files listed in the message."
msgstr ""
"Die signierte Message im oberen Teil der Datei listet mehrere Dateien "
"zusammen mit ihren jeweiligen SHA256 Hashes auf. Die aufgezählten Dateien "
"sind Installationspakete für alle Betriebssysteme und Architekturen, für die"
" Bitcoin Core freigegeben worden ist. Der untere Teil der Datei ist die "
"Signatur der Message im oberen Teil. Die Signatur bindet sich an die gesamte"
" Message und damit an alle Hashes und Dateien, die in der Message "
"aufgelistet werden."

#. type: Title =====
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1236
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifying the hash of the downloaded file"
msgstr "Überprüfen des Hashes der heruntergeladenen Datei"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1241
msgid ""
"The file you downloaded is named bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz so "
"you expect that the SHA256 hash of that file matches `9d6b…5a4f` exactly. "
"Let’s check:"
msgstr ""
"Die Datei, die du heruntergeladen hast, heisst bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-"
"gnu.tar.gz, also erwartest du, dass der SHA256 Hash dieser Datei mit "
"`9d6b…5a4f` übereinstimmt. Schauen wir mal nach:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1245
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ sha256sum bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz \n"
"9d6b472dc2aceedb1a974b93a3003a81b7e0265963bd2aa0acdcb17598215a4f  bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz\n"
msgstr ""
"$ sha256sum bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz \n"
"9d6b472dc2aceedb1a974b93a3003a81b7e0265963bd2aa0acdcb17598215a4f  bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1251
msgid ""
"This command calculates the SHA256 hash of your downloaded file. It does "
"indeed match the hash in the SHA256SUMS.asc file. If they don’t match, then "
"something is wrong, and you should halt the installation and investigate."
msgstr ""
"Das Kommando berechnet den SHA256 Hash deines heruntergeladenen Files. Er "
"stimmt tatsächlich mit dem Hash in der Datei SHA256SUMS.asc überein. Wenn "
"die beiden nicht übereinstimmen würden, dann würde irgendetwas nicht stimmen"
" und du solltest mit der Installation aufhören und nachschauen, was da los "
"ist."

#. type: Title =====
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1252
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting the Bitcoin Core signing key"
msgstr "Den Bitcoin Core Signier Key holen"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1263
msgid ""
"To verify that the signature in the signature file was done using the "
"Bitcoin Core signing key, you need the corresponding public key. As noted in"
" <<step-1>>, you should convince yourself about what fingerprint the Bitcoin"
" Core key has and then download that key from any source."
msgstr ""
"Um zu prüfen, dass die Signatur in der Signaturdatei mit dem Bitcoin Core "
"Key geleistet wurde, brauchst du den dazugehörigen public Key. Wie in "
"<<step-1>> erwähnt, musst du nachschauen, welchen Fingerprint der Bitcoin "
"Core Key besitzt, und dann diesen Key von irgendwo herunterladen."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1265
msgid "You could, for example,"
msgstr "Du könntest zum Beispiel:"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1269
msgid ""
"Get the fingerprint of the Bitcoin Core team’s key from "
"https://bitcoincore.org, the official website of the Bitcoin Core team."
msgstr ""
"Den Fingerprint des Bitcoin Core Teams von https://bitcoincore.org holen, "
"der offiziellen Webseite des Bitcoin Core Teams."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1271
msgid "Consult the book _Grokking Bitcoin_ to verify the fingerprint."
msgstr ""
"Im Buch _Bitcoin Begreifen_ nachschauen, um den Fingerprint zu prüfen."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1276
msgid ""
"Start by finding the Bitcoin Core team’s public key fingerprint on their "
"website. You find the following fingerprint on the downloads page:"
msgstr ""
"Fang damit an, dass du den Bitcoin Core Team public Key Fingerprint auf "
"deren Webseite suchst. Du findest den folgenden Fingerprint auf der Download"
" Seite:"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1278
#, no-wrap
msgid " 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
msgstr " 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1283
msgid ""
"Now, consult the book _Grokking Bitcoin_ to check if the fingerprint in that"
" book matches the fingerprint from https://bitcoincore.org. Look in the "
"<<step-1>> of <<ch08>> of that book. It says"
msgstr ""
"Jetzt schau in das Buch _Bitcoin Begreifen_, um zu prüfen, dass der "
"Fingerprint im Buch zu dem auf https://bitcoincore.org passt. Schau in "
"<<step-1>> von <<ch08>>. Dort steht"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1291
msgid ""
"This is the same fingerprint (although formatted slightly differently).  The"
" book and the website https://bitcoincore.org both claim that this key "
"belongs to the Bitcoin Core team. Let’s not settle for that. You’ll also "
"call a friend you trust and have her read the fingerprint to you:"
msgstr ""
"Das ist derselbe Fingerprint  (wenn auch etwas anders formatiert). Das Buch "
"und die Webseite https://bitcoincore.org behaupten beide, dass dieser Key "
"zum Bitcoin Core Team gehört. Verlassen wir uns aber nicht darauf. Du rufst "
"ausserdem einen Freund an und lässt dir den Fingerprint vorlesen:"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1294
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*You:* “Hello, Donna! What’s the fingerprint of the current Bitcoin Core\n"
"signing key?”\n"
msgstr ""
"*Du:* “Hallo, Donna! Wie lautet der Fingerprint des aktuellen Bitcoin Core\n"
"Signatur Keys?”\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1297
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Donna:* “Hi! I verified that key myself a few months ago, and I know\n"
"the fingerprint is `01EA 5486 DE18 A882 D4C2 6845 90C8 019E 36C2 E964`.”\n"
msgstr ""
"*Donna:* “Hi! Ich habe den selbst erst vor ein paar Monaten verifiziert und ich weiss, dass\n"
"der Fingerprint `01EA 5486 DE18 A882 D4C2 6845 90C8 019E 36C2 E964`. ist”\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1299
#, no-wrap
msgid "*You:* “Thank you, it matches mine. Goodbye!”\n"
msgstr "*Du:* “Danke, das stimmt mit meinem überein. Tschüss!”\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1301
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Donna:* “You’re welcome. Goodbye!”\n"
msgstr "*Donna:* “Bitteschön. Tschüss!”\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1304
msgid ""
"Donna’s statement further strengthens your trust in this key. You think "
"you’ve collected enough evidence that this is, in fact, the correct key."
msgstr ""
"Donnas Aussage verstärkt dein Vertrauen in diesen Key. Jetzt glaubst du, "
"genügend Beweise dafür zu haben, dass dies in der Tat der korrekte Key ist."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1310
msgid ""
"Let’s start downloading the key. To do this, you can use a tool called gpg, "
"which stands for GnuPG, which in turn stands for Gnu Privacy Guard.  This "
"program conforms to a standard called OpenPGP (Pretty Good Privacy). This "
"standard specifies how keys can be exchanged and how to do encryption and "
"digital signatures in an interoperable way."
msgstr ""
"Fangen wir damit an, den Key herunterzuladen. Um dies zu tun, kannst du ein "
"Tool namens gpg benutzen, was für GnuPG steht, was wiederum eine Abkürzung "
"für Gnu Privacy Guard ist. Dieses Programm entspricht einem Standard namens "
"OpenPGP (Pretty Good Privacy). Dieser Standard spezifiziert, wie Keys "
"ausgetauscht werden können, und wie Verschlüsselung und digitale Signaturen "
"in kompatibler Weise zu erledigen sind."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1314
msgid ""
"GnuPG is available on most Linux computers by default. To download a public "
"key with a certain fingerprint, you run the following `gpg` command:"
msgstr ""
"GnuPG ist auf den meisten Linux Computern per Default installiert. Um einen "
"public Key mit einem bestimmten Fingerprint zu laden, gibst du das folgende "
"`gpg` Kommando ein:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1321
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ gpg --recv-keys 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
"gpg: key 90C8019E36C2E964: public key \"Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\" imported\n"
"gpg: no ultimately trusted keys found\n"
"gpg: Total number processed: 1\n"
"gpg:               imported: 1\n"
msgstr ""
"$ gpg --recv-keys 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
"gpg: key 90C8019E36C2E964: public key \"Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\" imported\n"
"gpg: no ultimately trusted keys found\n"
"gpg: Total number processed: 1\n"
"gpg:               imported: 1\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1328
msgid ""
"Depending on the version of gpg you use, the output can vary. This command "
"downloads the public key from any available key server and verifies that the"
" downloaded public key in fact has the fingerprint that you requested. The "
"owner of this key is “Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release "
"signing key).”"
msgstr ""
"Je nachdem, welche Version von gpg du benutzt, kann der Output variieren. "
"Dieses Kommando lädt den public Key von einem verfügbaren Key Server und "
"verifiziert, dass der geladene public Key tatsächlich den Fingerprint "
"besitzt, den du angefordert hast. Der Besitzer des Keys ist “Wladimir J. van"
" der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key).”"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1334
msgid ""
"The prior command downloads the key into gpg and adds it to your list of "
"known keys. But the output of this command mentions “no ultimately trusted "
"keys found.” This means this key isn’t signed by any key that you trust. "
"You’ve only imported the key. In gpg, keys can sign other keys to certify "
"that the signed key is legit."
msgstr ""
"Der vorangegangene Befehl lädt den Key in gpg und fügt ihn deiner Liste "
"bekannter Keys hinzu. Aber im Output des Befehls steht “no ultimately "
"trusted keys found,” also “keine ultimativ vertrauenswürdigen Keys "
"gefunden.” Dies bedeutet, dass dieser Key nicht von irgendeinem Key, dem du "
"vertraust, signiert worden ist. Du hast den Key nur importiert. In gpg "
"können Keys andere Keys signieren, um deren Legitimität zu bezeugen."

#. type: Title =====
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1335
#, no-wrap
msgid "Signing the public key as trusted on your computer"
msgstr "Signiere den public Key auf deinem Computer als vertrauenswürdig "

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1339
msgid ""
"You’ve verified that the key belongs to the Bitcoin Core team and installed "
"that key onto your system using gpg."
msgstr ""
"Du hast verifiziert, dass der Key zum Bitcoin Core Team gehört und ihn "
"mittels gpg auf deinem System installiert."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1345
msgid ""
"You’ll now sign that key with a private key that you own. You do this to "
"remember this key as trusted. The Bitcoin Core team will probably release "
"new versions of Bitcoin Core in the future. If GnuPG remembers this public "
"key as trusted, you won’t have to go through all these key-verification "
"steps again when you upgrade."
msgstr ""
"Du wirst jetzt diesen Key mit einem private Key signieren, der dir gehört. "
"Das tust du, um dir zu merken, dass du diesem Key vertraust. Das Bitcoin "
"Core Team wird wahrscheinlich künftig weitere Versionen von Bitcoin Core "
"freigeben. Wenn GnuPG sich diesen public Key als vertrauenswürdig merkt, "
"musst du nicht mehr durch all diese Key-Verifikations-Schritte gehen, wenn "
"du einen Upgrade installierst."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1349
msgid "Create a key of your own."
msgstr "Erzeuge deinen eigenen Key."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1351
msgid "Sign the Bitcoin Core public key with your own private key."
msgstr "Signiere den Bitcoin Core public Key mit deinem eigenen private Key."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1353
msgid "GnuPG lets you create a key of your own with the following command:"
msgstr "GnuPG lässt dich mit folgendem Befehl einen eigenen Key erzeugen:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1359
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ gpg --gen-key\n"
"gpg (GnuPG) 2.1.18; Copyright (C) 2017 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\n"
"This is free software: you are free to change and redistribute it.\n"
"There is NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by law.\n"
msgstr ""
"$ gpg --gen-key\n"
"gpg (GnuPG) 2.1.18; Copyright (C) 2017 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\n"
"This is free software: you are free to change and redistribute it.\n"
"There is NO WARRANTY, to the extent permitted by law.\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1361
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Note: Use \"gpg --full-generate-key\" for a full featured key generation "
"dialog.\n"
msgstr ""
"Hinweis: Gib \"gpg --full-generate-key\" ein und du bekommst einen "
"vollständigen Key-Erzeugungs-Dialog.\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1363
#, no-wrap
msgid "GnuPG needs to construct a user ID to identify your key.\n"
msgstr ""
"GnuPG muss eine Benutzer ID konstruieren, um deinen Key zu identifizieren.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1367
msgid ""
"GnuPG will ask for your name and email address. Answer these questions; "
"they’ll be used to identify your key:"
msgstr ""
"GnuPG fragt nach deinem Namen und deiner Mailadresse. Beantworte diese "
"Fragen, denn sie dienen zur Identifizierung deines Keys:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1373
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Real name: Kalle Rosenbaum\n"
"Email address: kalle@example.com\n"
"You selected this USER-ID:\n"
"    \"Kalle Rosenbaum <kalle@example.com>\"\n"
msgstr ""
"Real name: Kalle Rosenbaum\n"
"Email address: kalle@example.com\n"
"You selected this USER-ID:\n"
"    \"Kalle Rosenbaum <kalle@example.com>\"\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1375
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change (N)ame, (E)mail, or (O)kay/(Q)uit? \n"
msgstr "Change (N)ame, (E)mail, or (O)kay/(Q)uit? \n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1380
msgid ""
"Continue by pressing O (capital letter “oh”). You then need to select a "
"password with which to encrypt your private key. Choose a password, and make"
" sure you remember it."
msgstr ""
"Mach weiter, indem du O drückst (den Grossbuchstaben “oh”). Dann musst du "
"dir ein Passwort ausdenken, mit dem der private Key verschlüsselt wird. Such"
" das Passwort aus, und sorge dafür, dass du es nicht vergisst oder "
"verlierst."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1384
msgid ""
"Key generation might take a while, because it takes time to generate good "
"random numbers for your key. When it’s finished, you should see output like "
"this:"
msgstr ""
"Die Key Erzeugung kann eine Weile dauern, weil es etwas Zeit braucht, für "
"den Key gute Zufallszahlen zu erzeugen. Wenn es fertig ist, solltest du "
"einen Output wie diesen sehen:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1387
#, no-wrap
msgid "public and secret key created and signed.\n"
msgstr "public and secret key created and signed.\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1393
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"pub   rsa2048 2018-04-27 [SC] [expires: 2020-04-26]\n"
"      B8C0D19BB7E17E5CEC6D69D487C0AC3FEDA7E796\n"
"      B8C0D19BB7E17E5CEC6D69D487C0AC3FEDA7E796\n"
"uid                      Kalle Rosenbaum <kalle@example.com>\n"
"sub   rsa2048 2018-04-27 [E] [expires: 2020-04-26]\n"
msgstr ""
"pub   rsa2048 2018-04-27 [SC] [expires: 2020-04-26]\n"
"      B8C0D19BB7E17E5CEC6D69D487C0AC3FEDA7E796\n"
"      B8C0D19BB7E17E5CEC6D69D487C0AC3FEDA7E796\n"
"uid                      Kalle Rosenbaum <kalle@example.com>\n"
"sub   rsa2048 2018-04-27 [E] [expires: 2020-04-26]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1397
msgid ""
"You now have a key of your own that you’ll use to sign keys that you trust. "
"Let’s sign the Bitcoin Core team key:"
msgstr ""
"Jetzt hast du einen eigenen Key, mit dem du Keys signieren kannst, denen du "
"vertraust. Signieren wir den Bitcoin Core Team Key:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1400
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ gpg --sign-key 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
msgstr "$ gpg --sign-key 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1405
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"pub  rsa4096/90C8019E36C2E964\n"
"     created: 2015-06-24  expires: 2019-02-14  usage: SC  \n"
"     trust: unknown       validity: unknown\n"
"[ unknown] (1). Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\n"
msgstr ""
"pub  rsa4096/90C8019E36C2E964\n"
"     created: 2015-06-24  expires: 2019-02-14  usage: SC  \n"
"     trust: unknown       validity: unknown\n"
"[ unknown] (1). Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1411
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"pub  rsa4096/90C8019E36C2E964\n"
"     created: 2015-06-24  expires: 2019-02-14  usage: SC  \n"
"     trust: unknown       validity: unknown\n"
" Primary key fingerprint: 01EA 5486 DE18 A882 D4C2  6845 90C8 019E 36C2 E964\n"
msgstr ""
"pub  rsa4096/90C8019E36C2E964\n"
"     created: 2015-06-24  expires: 2019-02-14  usage: SC  \n"
"     trust: unknown       validity: unknown\n"
" Primary key fingerprint: 01EA 5486 DE18 A882 D4C2  6845 90C8 019E 36C2 E964\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1413
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) "
"<laanwj@gmail.com>\n"
msgstr ""
"     Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) "
"<laanwj@gmail.com>\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1417
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This key is due to expire on 2019-02-14.\n"
"Are you sure that you want to sign this key with your\n"
"key \"Kalle Rosenbaum <kalle@example.com>\" (8DC7D3846BA6AB5E)\n"
msgstr ""
"This key is due to expire on 2019-02-14.\n"
"Are you sure that you want to sign this key with your\n"
"key \"Kalle Rosenbaum <kalle@example.com>\" (8DC7D3846BA6AB5E)\n"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1419
#, no-wrap
msgid "Really sign? (y/N)\n"
msgstr "Really sign? (y/N)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1425
msgid ""
"Enter `y`. You’ll be prompted for your private key password. Enter it, and "
"press Enter. The Bitcoin Core key should now be regarded as trusted by gpg. "
"This will simplify the process when you upgrade your node in the future."
msgstr ""
"Gib `y` ein. Dann wirst du nach dem Passwort des private Keys gefragt. Gib "
"es ein und drücke Enter. Der Bitcoin Core Key sollte jetzt von gpg als "
"vertrauenswürdig eingestuft worden sein. Das vereinfacht den Ablauf, wenn du"
" künftig einen Upgrade der Node Software einspielen willst."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1427
msgid "Let’s look at your newly signed key:"
msgstr "Schauen wir uns den neu signierten Key einmal an:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1433
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ gpg --list-keys 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
"pub   rsa4096 2015-06-24 [SC] [expires: 2019-02-14]\n"
"      01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
"uid           [  full  ] Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\n"
msgstr ""
"$ gpg --list-keys 01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
"pub   rsa4096 2015-06-24 [SC] [expires: 2019-02-14]\n"
"      01EA5486DE18A882D4C2684590C8019E36C2E964\n"
"uid           [  full  ] Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1437
msgid ""
"The word to look for is `full` in square brackets. This means gpg, and you, "
"fully trust this key."
msgstr ""
"Das Wort, das wir suchen, ist `full` in eckigen Klammern. Das bedeutet, dass"
" gpg und du, ihr beide dem Key vollständig vertraut."

#. type: Title =====
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1438
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verifying the signature"
msgstr "Verifizieren der Signatur"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1441
msgid "It’s time to verify the signature of the SHA256SUMS.asc file:"
msgstr "Es ist Zeit, die Signatur der SHA256SUMS.asc Datei zu verifizieren:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1447
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ gpg --verify SHA256SUMS.asc \n"
"gpg: Signature made Wed 03 Oct 2018 10:53:25 AM CEST\n"
"gpg:                using RSA key 90C8019E36C2E964\n"
"gpg: Good signature from \"Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\" [full]\n"
msgstr ""
"$ gpg --verify SHA256SUMS.asc \n"
"gpg: Signature made Wed 03 Oct 2018 10:53:25 AM CEST\n"
"gpg:                using RSA key 90C8019E36C2E964\n"
"gpg: Good signature from \"Wladimir J. van der Laan (Bitcoin Core binary release signing key) <laanwj@gmail.com>\" [full]\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1451
msgid ""
"It says that the signature is `Good` and that it’s signed with a key that "
"you fully trust, `[full]`."
msgstr ""
"Da steht, dass die Signatur `Good` ist und mit einem Schlüssel signiert ist,"
" dem du voll und ganz vertraust, `[full]`."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1453
msgid "To summarize, you’ve done the following:"
msgstr "Zusammenfassend hast du Folgendes getan:"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1455
msgid "Downloaded Bitcoin Core and the signature file"
msgstr "Bitcoin Core und die Signaturdatei heruntergeladen"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1458
msgid ""
"Verified that the hash of the .tar.gz file matches the stated hash in "
"SHA256SUMS.asc"
msgstr ""
"Überprüft, ob der Hash der Datei .tar.gz mit dem in SHA256SUMS.asc "
"angegebenen Hash übereinstimmt"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1460
msgid "Downloaded a public key and verified that it belongs to Bitcoin Core"
msgstr ""
"Einen public Key heruntergeladen und überprüft, ob er zu Bitcoin Core gehört"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1463
msgid ""
"Signed that key with your own private key so GnuPG and you remember that the"
" Bitcoin Core key is legit"
msgstr ""
"Den Key mit deinem eigenen private Key signiert, damit GnuPG und du sich "
"merken, dass der Bitcoin Core Key legitim ist"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1465
msgid "Verified the signature of the SHA256SUMS.asc file"
msgstr "Die Signatur der Datei SHA256SUMS.asc verifiziert"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1468
msgid ""
"When you later upgrade the program, you can skip several of these steps.  "
"The process will then be"
msgstr ""
"Wenn du das Programm später upgraden willst, kannst du mehrere dieser "
"Schritte überspringen. Der Prozess beschränkt sich dann auf diese Schritte"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1470
msgid "Download Bitcoin Core and the signature file."
msgstr "Bitcoin Core und die Signaturdatei herunterladen."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1473
msgid ""
"Verify that the hash of the .tar.gz file matches the stated hash in "
"SHA256SUMS.asc."
msgstr ""
"Prüfen, dass der Hash der .tar.gz Datei mit dem Hash in SHA256SUMS.ac "
"übereinstimmt."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1475
msgid "Verify the signature of the SHA256SUMS.asc file."
msgstr "Die Signatur der SHA256SUMS.asc Datei überprüfen."

#. type: Title ====
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1477
#, no-wrap
msgid "Unpacking and starting"
msgstr "Auspacken und starten"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1480
msgid "Let’s unpack the software:"
msgstr "Packen wir die Software aus:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1483
#, no-wrap
msgid "tar -zxvf bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz\n"
msgstr "tar -zxvf bitcoin-0.17.0-x86_64-linux-gnu.tar.gz\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1487
msgid ""
"This will create a directory called bitcoin-0.17.0. Go into the directory "
"bitcoin-0.17.0/bin, and have a look:"
msgstr ""
"Das erzeugt ein Verzeichnis namens bitcoin-0.17.0. Gehe in das Verzeichnis "
"bitcoin-0.17.0/bin und schau dich um:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd bitcoin-0.17.0/bin\n"
"$ ls\n"
"bitcoin-cli  bitcoind  bitcoin-qt  bitcoin-tx  test_bitcoin\n"
msgstr ""
"$ cd bitcoin-0.17.0/bin\n"
"$ ls\n"
"bitcoin-cli  bitcoind  bitcoin-qt  bitcoin-tx  test_bitcoin\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1495
msgid "Here you have several executable programs:"
msgstr "Hier hast du mehrere ausführbare Programme:"

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1499
msgid ""
"bitcoin-cli is a program you can use to extract information about the node "
"you’re running as well as manage a built-in wallet that’s shipped with "
"Bitcoin Core."
msgstr ""
"bitcoin-cli ist ein Programm, mit dem sowohl man Informationen über den "
"Node, der auf dem Computer läuft, herauskriegen kann, als auch das "
"eingebaute Wallet verwalten kann, das bei Bitcoin Core mitgeliefert wird."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1502
msgid ""
"bitcoind is the program to use if you want to run the node in the background"
" without a graphical user interface (GUI)."
msgstr ""
"Das Programm bitcoind benutzt man, wenn man den Node im Hintergrund ohne "
"grafische Benutzerschnittstelle (GUI) laufen lassen will."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1505
msgid ""
"bitcoin-qt is the program to run if you want a GUI for your node. This is "
"mainly useful if you use the built-in wallet."
msgstr ""
"Das Programm bitcoin-qt benutzt man, wenn man ein GUI für den Node braucht. "
"Das ist nützlich, wenn man das eingebaute Wallet benutzt."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1508
msgid ""
"bitcoin-tx is a small utility program to create and modify Bitcoin "
"transactions."
msgstr ""
"Das Programm bitcoin-tx ist ein kleines Hilfsprogramm zum Erzeugen und "
"Modifizieren von Bitcoin Transaktionen."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1510
msgid "test_bitcoin lets you test run a test suite."
msgstr "Und es gibt noch test_bitcoin, was eine Test-Suite für Bitcoin ist."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1514
msgid ""
"In this tutorial, you’ll run bitcoind, which stands for “Bitcoin daemon.” In"
" UNIX systems such as Linux, the word _daemon_ is used for computer programs"
" that run in the background."
msgstr ""
"In diesem Tutorial benutzen wir bitcoind, was für “Bitcoin daemon” steht. In"
" UNIX Systemen wie Linux bezeichnet das Wort _daemon_ Computerprogramme, die"
" im Hintergrund laufen."

#. type: Plain text
#: ch08-peer-to-peer-network.adoc:1517
msgid ""
"Let’s start the Bitcoin Core daemon in the background and see what happens:"
msgstr ""
"Starten wir den Bitcoin Core Daemon im Hintergrund und schauen, was "
